  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "Stack overflow in paddle.searchsorted\u00a0in PaddlePaddle before 2.6.0. This flaw can lead to a denial of service, or even more damage.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2023-52304 concerns PaddlePaddle, a major AI framework. The vulnerability is a software defect (stack overflow) in a component used within ML pipelines, with potential denial of service and broader impact. This sits squarely in the software supply chain for general-purpose AI systems, and there is public CVE/NVD advisory coverage. Therefore, it meets criteria for AI relevance, supply-chain relevance, security risk, and sufficient evidence."
